  "prompt": "Is it a felony to launder money?",
  "response": "Yes, in the United States and many other countries, money laundering is a felony.\n\n*   **United States:** Under federal law (18 U.S.C. \u00a7 1956 and 1957), money laundering is a felony punishable by significant fines and imprisonment. The specific penalties depend on the amount of money laundered, the nature of the underlying criminal activity, and other factors.\n*   **Internationally:** Most countries have laws criminalizing money laundering as a felony, often with serious penalties to combat organized crime and terrorism financing.\n\nThe severity and specific elements of the crime can vary slightly by jurisdiction, but the core principle of concealing the source of illegally obtained funds is generally a felony-level offense.",
